                             LOADING INSTRUCTIONS
                             ====================

 Running from floppy disk :
 --------------------------
   I think you know the score by now !

 Installing to hard drive :
 --------------------------
    These instructions assume a working knowledge of Amiga workbench.
 1   Boot from your hard drive and wait for the workbench to load.
 2   Insert disk #1 into any drive.
 3   Drag the install program from disk #1 to your hard drive where you want to
     install the game.(A new draw containing Hired Guns will be created.)
 4   Run the copy of the install prog.
 5   The installation program allows a partial installation of the game.  For
    most users however just stick with the default settings and click on the
    install button at the bottom left.
 6   Insert each disk as requested.
 7   Once the installation is finished the game is ready to run.  You may need
 to update the workbench display to show the new icons.  Simply close the draw
 containing Hired Guns on your hard drive then re-open it again.


 Making back up copies of your disks :
 -------------------------------------
   Simply copy the disks with the DISKCOPY command or any third party disk
  copier.


                           EXTRA MEMORY ENHANCEMENTS
                           =========================

   If your Amiga has at least 1.5mb of memory and if 1mb of this is graphics
 memory then Hired Guns will feature greatly enhanced sound effects.  An extra
 410k of data will be loaded from disk #5 when you boot the game.  The monsters
 will now make noises, thunder will rumble in the distance and there will be a
 far greater variety of gunfire effects.

   If you still have memory left over Hired Guns will allow you to snapshot a
 saved game to memory.  This snapshot will be lost if you reset your Amiga or
 exit a level so be sure to save anything important to disk.

   If you are playing Hired Guns from a hard disk and have 2mb of memory, then
 you may have problems getting the extra sound effects.  Depending on your
 machine's configuration the workbench will consume a varying amount of memory -
 possibly leaving Hired Guns with too little.

   To leave as much memory as possible for Hired Guns will require bypassing
 the hard disk boot sequence.  To do this boot from disk #1.  When the workbench
 appears run the game from your hard drive as usual.


 DISK ACCESSING :
 ----------------
   For users playing Hired Guns directly from floppy disk with fewer than 4
 external disk drives ( HUH !! ) There will be a need to swap disks during the
 game.  The data files have been placed in such a position as to minimise the
 need for swapping and there is no swapping during actual gameplay.

   When a disk is required, follow the on screen prompts to access the relevant
 game data.  Note the prompt to the top right hand corner of the panel
 identifying the next disk that will be required.  This allows disk access time
 to be optimised.



