   JOYPAD CONTROLS
   ---------------
   The advantage of using the joypad over a joystick is that it gives the user
 3 extra buttons.  This makes it much more convenient for manipulating items.
 The drawback is that a SEGA MEGADRIVE joypad ( spit,spit ) will have to be
 modified internally for use with the Amiga (without the modification the pad
 will only function as a joystick with two buttons)

  To make the modification, get the sticky back plastic and round nosed scissors
 out.  only joking!!!   Simply swap lines 5 & 7 over.
                        -----------------------------
 This is easily accomplished by opening up the joypad and de-soldering the
 relavant lines to the circuit board then swapping them over.

